comments: Dekker (WAS) places his hand momentarily on Sampson's (CHI) hip before correcting.
RAR shows McRae (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Harrison's (CHI) driving shot attempt.
Sampson (CHI) legally contests Dekker's (WAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Felicio (CHI) is already in Randle's (WAS) path and he absorbs the contact to his arms.
RLB shows Bryant (WAS) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Lemon Jr.'s (CHI) shot attempt.
McRae (WAS) makes incidental contact with Harrison (CHI) that does not affect his ability to defend.
LAR shows Felicio (CHI) maintains legal guarding position as he defends McRae's (WAS) drive.
Bryant (WAS) is already in Harrison's (CHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
RAR shows Alkins (CHI) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
RAR shows McRae (WAS) steps out of bounds during his drive.
RLS shows McRae (WAS) legally contests Harrison's (CHI) shot near the rim.
LAR and RAR show Brown Jr. (WAS) legally contests Harrison's (CHI) shot near the rim.
LAR shows Felicio (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Bryant (WAS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Felicio (CHI) engages with Bryant (WAS) during the inbound but does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
LAR and LLS show Felicio (CHI) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Bryant's (WAS) shot attempt.
Felicio (CHI) is already in Randle's (WAS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
MOB shows Bryant (WAS) does not maintain legal guarding position, and he makes contact to Lemon Jr.'s (CHI) arm as he defends the shot near the rim.
[Observable in enhanced video] Lemon Jr. (CHI) moves his pivot foot during his spin move.
LLB shows Harrison (CHI) makes marginal contact to McRae's (WAS) arm during his drive.  This contact occurs prior to McRae's gather and upward shooting motion and would not warrant a shooting foul.
LLB shows Harrison (CHI) cleanly dislodges the ball from McRae (WAS).
Harrison (CHI) jumps into Randle's (WAS) body and affects his shot near the rim.
McRae (WAS) commits a take foul on Harrison (CHI).
MOB shows Lemon (CHI) swings his arm through and initiates contact to Randle's (WAS) face which affects his ability to defend the driving shot attempt.
RAR and LAR show Harrison (CHI) legally defends McRae's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
